    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-18T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="564"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.20252/218: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-18T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 18, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 19—3:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3401. My 3323, November 12.<note n="46" xml:id="d564fn46">Not Printed.</note> I
                    told Jordana this morning that my Government was greatly troubled over the
                    inordinate number of German agents throughout Spain including active Nazi party
                    members, <pb facs="0642" n="630" xml:id="pg_630"/> members of the Gestapo, and
                    sabotage and espionage agents. Moreover, we are aware that the number of these
                    agents had increased recently. We are aware also of increasing German pressure
                    on unneutral elements in Falange. I said I would reserve for the future further
                    discussion of this matter in its larger aspects but at this time specifically I
                    wished to state that the United States Government joined the British Government
                    in requesting prompt suppression of the German Consulate General at Tangier and
                    expulsion of German agents from there. I said we had abundant evidence that
                    Tangier is an important base of operations of the German agents I had referred
                    to. I then handed him a note on the subject.</p>
                <p>Jordana limited his reply to saying he would study the note.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tangier.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
